Understanding Data-Driven Decision-Making
  Data-driven decision-making involves using facts to guide business strategies.
  It starts with identifying a business need or problem that requires a solution.

Role of Data Analysts
  Data analysts gather and analyze data to uncover trends and patterns.
  They help organizations make informed decisions based on data insights.

Real-World Applications
  Streaming services use data to recommend content based on user preferences.
  E-commerce has evolved due to data insights, leading to new business models that prioritize online shopping.
